        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Completion of the Online Course",
          "Pass (1) vs Fail (0)",
          "1265 FOC learners, 2304 QDS learners, MOSFETs learners",
          "Fiber Optic Communications, Quantum Detectors and Sensors and Essentials of MOSFETs graduate courses in Purdue University",
          "Student characteristics, LMS logs",
          "[watch_noquiz, watch_correct, watch_incorrect, watch_noanswer, forum_post, forum_reply, forum_view, gender, country, year of birth]",
          "End of Course",
          "Different activity types are represented with One-hot encoding. The nature of the data is being sequential -Activities are recorded for each timestep.\n\nIn addition, the students are separated bby different student subgroups.\n\nTraining is done with recourse to Self-Supervised learning: local-global that customizes predictions for each subgroup.\n\nWeight updates are done with recourse to attention mechanisms.\n",
          "GRU, LSTM, AttnGRU-L, AttnGRU-G, FedAvg, FedAttn, FedIRT, Ourts-AtttnAgg, ",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "FOC\n{AUC: [0.62,  0.83] - Ours}\n\nQDS\n{AUC: [0.656,  0.789] - Ours}\n\nMOSFETS\n{AUC: [0.613,  0.748] - Ours}",
          "Authors train models for different subbgroups -Gender, Continent and Year of Birth. \n\nThe experiments includee testing the training of models speficic for subgroups vs more “global models”. Results show that the Personalized Models (Local with Self-Supervised Learning) consistently outperform the Global altrernatives.\n\nImprovements of separability are also noticeable via t-SNE visualizations",
          "- Student subgroups weer defined by human criteria\n\nNo general results (irrespective of subgroup) are shown, which hinders interpretability of results."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
